Introduction

EPEX, formerly known as C9ROOKIES, is a 8-member South Korean boy group under C9 Entertainment, consisting of Wish, Keum, Mu, A-Min, Baek Seung, Ayden, Yewang, and Jeff. They debuted on June 8, 2021, with their first EP album ‘Bipolar Pt.1 Prelude of Anxiety’.

Their group name is described as "the gathering of Eight youths reaches eight different aPEXes", meaning that the 8 members are forming a collective, powerful new team.
